/**
\mainpage misc : Miscellaneous functions

<b>Brief description</b>\n
The 'Miscellaneous Functions' (misc) module is a collection of useful functions, meant to be used by every sort of programs and libraries.

<b>Detailed decription</b>\n
As of today, the misc module contains functions to deal with :
\li \b date: get local and UTC time (miscDate.c)
\li <b> dynamic buffer </b>: auto-expanding, byte-based buffer (miscDynBuf.c)
\li \b files: UNIX-like file path computing, and environment variables resolving
(miscFile.c)
\li \b network: network-related utility functions (miscNetwork.c)
\li \b strings: null-terminated string computing, like quotes stripping and
upper casing (miscString.c)
\li \b hash table: hash table handling (miscHash.c)
*/
